ngth\n1 <= m, n <= 20\n0 <= matrix[i][j] <= 99\n\n \nFollow up:\n\nWhat if the matrix is stored on disk, and the memory is limited such that you can only load at most one row of the matrix into the memory at once?\nWhat if the matrix is so large that you can only load up a partial row into the memory at once?\n\n\n\n### Format: You will use the following starter code to write the solution to the problem and enclose your code within delimiters.\n```python\nclass Solution:\n    def isToeplitzMatrix(self, matrix: List[List[int]]) -> bool:\n        \n```\n\n### Answer: (use the provided format with backticks)\n", "response": "```python\nfrom typing import List\n\nclass Solution:\n    def isToeplitzMatrix(self, matrix: List[List[int]]) -> bool:\n        # Check each element against the element diagonally above-left\n        for i in range(1, len(matrix)):\n            for j in range(1, len(matrix[0])):\n                if matrix[i][j] != matrix[i - 1][j - 1]:\n                    return False\n        return True\n```\n\nThis solution iterates through the matrix starting from the second row and second column, comparing each element with the element diagonally above and to the left. If any pair of elements do not match, the function returns `False`. If all pairs match, the function returns `True`, indicating that the matrix is Toeplitz.\n\nFor the follow-up questions:\n1. If the matrix is stored on disk and memory is limited to loading only one row at a time, you can compare each row with the previous row as you load them. Specifically, you only need to compare the current row (except the first element) with the previous row (except the last element).\n2. If the matrix is so large that you can only load a partial row into memory at once, you can use a sliding window approach. Load a chunk of the current row and the corresponding chunk of the previous row, and compare them. Continue this process until you have checked the entire row. This approach ensures that you only keep a small portion of each row in memory at any given time.", "estimated_date": 1438905600000}